{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Aim-1.2/mops_modifier_02.svg", "type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "Aim", "version": "1.2", "namespace": "MOPS"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Aim"], "extent": [0, 14]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aims MOPs primitives towards target points."], "extent": [52, 103]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The MOPs Aim Modifier orients packed primitives towards a target point, or multiple target points."], "extent": [103, 203]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["An orientation requires two vectors: an ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["aim vector"]}, " and an ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["up vector"]}, ". The aim vector determines which way the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["front"]}, " (by default, +Z) of each object will point towards. The up vector determines which way the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["top"]}, " (by default, +Y) of each object will point towards.\nYou can change these default axes using the Aim Axis and Up Axis parameters under the Orientation tab."], "extent": [203, 577]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [577, 592], "body": []}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [592, 601], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Primitives"], "extent": [601, 619], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The packed primitives to orient."], "extent": [619, 661]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Target"], "extent": [661, 673], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A SOP for the packed primitives to aim towards. In Aim at Object mode, the centroid of this SOP is used as the target. If no SOP is provided, a default control is used. In Aim At Points mode, each point is individually aimed at a matching point in this input."], "extent": [673, 942]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Target"], "extent": [942, 953], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A SOP for the packed primitives to use as an up vector. In Up to Object mode, the centroid of this SOP is used as the target. If no SOP is provided, a default control is used. In Up to Points mode, each point is individually aimed at a matching point in this input."], "extent": [953, 1228]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1228, 1240], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["General"], "extent": [1240, 1255], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [1255, 1263], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The group of packed primitives to affect."], "extent": [1278, 1329]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "group"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Do Falloff"], "extent": [1329, 1341], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable the falloff attribute. The aim orientation will be blended with the original orientation based on this attribute\u2019s value."], "extent": [1361, 1499]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_falloff"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Falloff Attribute"], "extent": [1499, 1518], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The name of the point attribute to use as the falloff attribute."], "extent": [1545, 1619]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "falloff_attribute"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim"], "extent": [1619, 1629], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Method"], "extent": [1629, 1642], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which the aim vector is determined"], "extent": [1662, 1716], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Aim Vector: The aim vector is determined from a single constant or an optional vector attribute."], "extent": [1716, 1823]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Aim at Object: The aim vector is determined by pointing each object towards the center of a control object."], "extent": [1823, 1941]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Aim at Points: The aim vector is determined from pointing towards matching points in the second input."], "extent": [1941, 2059]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_method"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Vector"], "extent": [2059, 2078], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Vector"], "extent": [2078, 2091], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The vector to aim towards. This applies globally to all points unless Use Attribute is enabled."], "extent": [2104, 2209]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Attribute"], "extent": [2209, 2224], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enables the use of a point attribute to aim towards. This must be a vector attribute."], "extent": [2242, 2337]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "use_attr"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute Name"], "extent": [2337, 2353], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The name of the vector attribute to use as the aim vector."], "extent": [2371, 2439]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_attr"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim at Object"], "extent": [2439, 2461], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Position"], "extent": [2461, 2476], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The position to aim towards. If an object is connected to the second input, the centroid of the object is used instead."], "extent": [2493, 2626]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_pos"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim at Points"], "extent": [2626, 2648], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Match Attribute"], "extent": [2648, 2666], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The attribute to use when matching the target points in the second input to the points to aim. This must be an integer point attribute."], "extent": [2686, 2831]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "match_attr"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up"], "extent": [2831, 2840], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Method"], "extent": [2840, 2852], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which the up vector is determined"], "extent": [2871, 2924], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Up Vector: The up vector is determined from a single constant or an optional vector attribute."], "extent": [2924, 3029]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Up to Object: The up vector is determined by pointing each object\u2019s top towards the center of a control object."], "extent": [3029, 3151]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Up to Points: The up vector is determined from pointing towards matching points in the second input."], "extent": [3151, 3263]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_method"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Vector"], "extent": [3263, 3281], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up"], "extent": [3281, 3286], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The vector to align the top of each point to. This applies globally to all points unless Use Attribute is enabled."], "extent": [3298, 3422]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Attribute"], "extent": [3422, 3437], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enables the use of a point attribute to use as the up vector. This must be a vector attribute."], "extent": [3456, 3560]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "use_attr2"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute Name"], "extent": [3560, 3576], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The name of the vector attribute to use as the up vector."], "extent": [3593, 3660]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_attr"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up to Object"], "extent": [3660, 3681], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Position"], "extent": [3681, 3695], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The position to orient the tops of points towards. If an object is connected to the second input, the centroid of the object is used instead."], "extent": [3711, 3862]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_pos"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up to Points"], "extent": [3862, 3883], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Match Attribute"], "extent": [3883, 3901], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The attribute to use when matching the target points in the third input to the points to aim. This must be an integer point attribute."], "extent": [3922, 4066]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "match_attr2"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Orientation"], "extent": [4066, 4084], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Aim Axis"], "extent": [4084, 4095], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The local axis to use as the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["forward"]}, " axis for each point. By default this is +Z."], "extent": [4113, 4205]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "aim_axis"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Axis"], "extent": [4205, 4214], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The local axis to use as the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["up"]}, " axis for each point. By default this is +Y."], "extent": [4231, 4318]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_axis"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert Aim"], "extent": [4318, 4330], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Flip the aim axis so that points are looking ", {"type": "q", "text": ["backwards"]}, "."], "extent": [4350, 4417]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_aim"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert Up"], "extent": [4417, 4428], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Flip the up axis so that points are looking ", {"type": "q", "text": ["upside down"]}, "."], "extent": [4447, 4515]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Constrain Around Up"], "extent": [4515, 4536], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Force objects to only be able to spin around their up axis instead of aiming directly at the target."], "extent": [4563, 4673]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [4673, 4682], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["When building the aim matrix in any software, the way you force a constraint to only operate on one plane is by swapping the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["up"]}, " and ", {"type": "q", "text": ["aim"]}, " targets and local axes. This can be done manually in older versions of MOPs Aim using VEXpressions, but this toggle is much easier."], "extent": [4682, 4961]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "constrain_up_axis"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["MOPs Aim"], "summary": ["Aims MOPs primitives towards target points."]}